IAM - Identity Access Management

Allows to you manager users and their level of access to the AWS console

Features:

  - Centralised control of your AWS account
  - Shared access to your AWS account
  - Granular permissions
  - Identity Federation (including Active Directory, Facebook, Linkedin.. etc)
  - MA (Multifactor Authentication)
  - Provide temporary access for user/devices when necessary
  - Allow to set up your password rotate policy
  - Integrate with many AWS services

Terminology:

  - Users: End users such people, employees of an organization
  - Groups: A collection of Users, the group will inherit the permissions of the group
  - Policies: JSON file they give permissions as what a User/Group/Role is able to do
  - Role: Assign to AWS resources
 

